    • Method Detail

      • setForwardConeAngle

        public AlertsManager.IncidentAlertOptions setForwardConeAngle(float value)
        Sets the angle of the cone to search ahead for incidents.

        By default this angle is set to AlertsManagerConfig.getForwardConeAngle() degrees. Valid values must fall between AlertsManager.IncidentAlertOptions.FORWARD_CONE_ANGLE_MIN and AlertsManager.IncidentAlertOptions.FORWARD_CONE_ANGLE_MAX.

        Parameters:
        value - The forward cone angle value in degrees.
        Returns:
        This instance of the AlertsManager.IncidentAlertOptions class.
        Throws:
        AlertsManager.AlertsManagerException - When the forward cone angle is out of range.

      • setSpeedFactor

        public T setSpeedFactor(float value)
        Sets the speed factor. This value is used to dynamically determine incident distance depending on current speed. For instance, if the speed factor is set to 10 and the current speed is 60mph, the alert manager will request incidents in a 6 miles radius (60mph / 10 = 6). A higher speed will result in a bigger radius in which to request incidents.
        Parameters:
        value - The speed factor, which should be positive number. Default value is AlertsManagerConfig.getSpeedFactor().
        Returns:
        This instance of the class.
        Throws:
        AlertsManager.AlertsManagerException - Thrown when the speed factor is invalid.
